# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-268
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Doubling, halving, quotative and partitive division"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will double and halve 2-digit numbers. They will explore division as both grouping and sharing and learn to use times table facts to find the quotient for 2x 5x 10x tables."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on knowledge of times tables and understanding of doubling and halving to develop understanding of the different structure of division: quotative (grouping) and partitive (sharing). Pupils also look for patterns in the 2-, 5- and 10-times tables and explore rules of divisibility based on the patterns. This is developed in future units and applied to larger numbers and other times tables.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall doubles and halves of numbers up to 20
Use sharing and grouping with small quantities
Understand division as the inverse of multiplication""" ;
  curric:id "268"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.416523Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-multiplication-and-division ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-fractions .

oakcurric:unit-257
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Grouping objects in different ways and relating to multiplication"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will describe how objects are grouped and will represent equal groups as repeated addition and multiplication."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit moves pupils on from thinking only about addition and introduces the concept and symbol for multiplication. Pupils explore how objects can be grouped and how to represent that grouping as multiplication as well as addition. This prepares them for work exploring the 2, 5 and 10 times tables.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Make equal groups and count the total
Use repeated addition as a strategy
Recognise arrays and relate to multiplication facts""" ;
  curric:id "257"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.426153Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-multiplication-and-division .

oakcurric:unit-264
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Money: recognise coins and use £ and p symbols"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will recognise and use symbols for pounds and pence combining amounts to make particular values. They will solve simple problems including giving change."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides the opportunity to revisit number facts and calculation strategies in the context of money. Pupils also build on earlier number and money work to make and convert quantities, give change and learn about pounds and pence notation.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise coin and note values
Use symbols £ and p appropriately
Apply number facts to money contexts""" ;
  curric:id "264"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.427737Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-256
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Adding and subtracting ones and tens to and from 2-digit numbers"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will add and subtract 1s and 10s from 2 digit numbers. They will use number facts to add/subtract a single-digit number to/from a 2-digit number. They will use a part-part-whole model to represent addition and subtraction."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit applies the number fact and place value work of the previous units to working with numbers beyond 20. Pupils use familiar representations: part-part-whole models and number lines, to support partitioning and bridging through tens.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count to 100
Understand place value of tens and ones
Partition numbers in different ways""" ;
  curric:id "256"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.428281Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-242
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Additive structures: addition and subtraction"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will find missing addends in equations. They will partition a whole into 2 parts representing first, then, now stories with subtraction equations. They will learn + and - are inverse operations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops the use of symbols to represent addition and subtraction stories and contexts. Pupils apply their understanding of the relationship between part-part-whole structures and addition and extend that to include subtraction representing decreasing an amount. Pupils also develop their understanding of the link between addition and subtraction using the inverse.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand part-whole relationships
Recognise inverse nature of addition and subtraction
Use equations and bar models to represent problems""" ;
  curric:id "242"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.481884Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-246
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Unitising and coin recognition - counting in 2s, 5s and 10s"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will count efficiently in groups of 2 5 10. They will recognise and explain the value of 1p 2p 5p 10p coins and how a single coin can be worth several pennies.¬†"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces 2, 5 and 10 p coins. Pupils explore objects and coins that represent more than one unit. They recognize the value of the coins and use the coins to support skip counting in 2, 10 and 5. This develops their counting and begins to prepare them for ideas of multiplicative thinking in Year 2 and onwards.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number facts and sequences
Use place value understanding
Apply basic operations in context""" ;
  curric:id "246"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.563658Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-multiplication-and-division .

oakcurric:unit-239
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Recognise, compose, decompose and manipulate 2D and 3D shapes"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will compose, copy, extend and develop repeating and radiating patterns. They will explore, discuss and compare 3D and 2D shapes."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides a break from developing number work and an opportunity to develop other key mathematical skills of special reasoning and pattern. The unit builds on the spatial reasoning and pattern language and examples they will have encountered in the Early Years.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify and describe 2D and 3D shapes
Explore how shapes can be combined or taken apart
Understand symmetry and simple transformations""" ;
  curric:id "239"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.564213Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-267
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Position and direction"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will order and arrange combinations of objects in patterns and sequences. They will consolidate and then extend understanding of position, direction"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit consolidates understanding of whole, half, quarter and three-quarter using mathematical vocabulary to describe patterns, position direction and movement. This prepares pupils for work involving right angles in the future.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use directional language such as left, right, forward, and back
Understand quarter, half, and full turns
Identify and describe position using a grid or map""" ;
  curric:id "267"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.564753Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-245
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Numbers 0 to 20 in different contexts"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will consolidate their counting to 20. They will measure objects using non-standard and standard measures and record outcomes, providing a context for counting and comparing numbers to 20."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides further opportunities for pupils to secure the counting sequence to 20 by exploring the numbers in different contexts beginning with non-standard measure and beginning to introduce length in centimetres. Pupils record the numbers to 20 in tables as part of their work and begin to make estimates based on what they know already.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise and count objects to 20
Represent numbers using words, digits and models
Compare quantities and solve simple problems""" ;
  curric:id "245"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.565284Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-252
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Counting and representing the numbers 20 to 99"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will explore the counting sequence for counting to 100 and beyond representing numbers from 20-99 in different ways including marking the position on a number line They will learn to represent 20-99 in the context of length."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In Year 2, pupils explored and rehearsed counting patterns from 20 to 99. In this unit they relate this knowledge of the patterns to different representations of place value.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count forwards and backwards from 0 to 100
Partition two-digit numbers into tens and ones
Represent numbers using concrete and pictorial models""" ;
  curric:id "252"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.565794Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-240
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Composition of numbers 6 to 10"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will represent numbers 6 - 10 by partitioning in different ways. They will learn what odd and even numbers are and how they can be partitioned. They will identify a missing part when a whole is partitioned into two parts where one of the parts is known."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on exploring numbers to five by looking at five and a bit to explore the numbers 6 – 10. Cardinal and ordinal aspects of number are explored through representations including a number line. Pupils explore and describe patterns of odd and even numbers and extend their understanding of parts and wholes to include numbers to ten.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count and represent numbers to 10
Partition numbers into different pairs
Use concrete resources to explore number combinations""" ;
  curric:id "240"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.566329Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-243
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Addition and subtraction facts within 10"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will explain that addition is commutative. They will find pairs of numbers to 10 and add or subtract 1 from any number.¬†Pupils will also develop their knowledge and understanding of odd and even numbers and that even numbers relate to doubling and halving."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops understanding and recording of addition and subtraction through exploring number facts within ten. Pupils develop and rehearse their knowledge of the composition of the numbers to ten and explore patterns including odd and even numbers again. They will begin to explore the concepts of doubling and halving as they relate to addition and subtraction facts.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number facts and sequences
Use place value understanding
Apply basic operations in context""" ;
  curric:id "243"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.566871Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-263
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Addition and subtraction of two 2-digit numbers"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils apply their knowledge of known facts and understanding of place value to add and subtract with 2-digit numbers both within and across the tens boundary."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on and applies knowledge of single digit facts and applies this to larger numbers. Pupils explain different addition and subtraction strategies and decide on the most efficient one for a given equation or problem. These strategies will be developed in future units to handle larger numbers.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number bonds to 20
Understand place value of tens and ones
Use column or number line methods for addition and subtraction""" ;
  curric:id "263"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.581592Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-statistics ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-241
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Additive structures: addition"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will combine 2 or more parts to make a whole. They will learn addends can be represented in any order and that the = sign shows the whole and sum of the parts are equal."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces the symbolic representation of addition and subtraction. Learning builds on the understanding of the part-part-whole structure and the composition of the numbers to 10, introducing the use of equations to represent known relationships before moving on, in later units, to solving problems involving addition.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand part-part-whole relationships
Represent problems using bar models and equations
Use different strategies for solving addition problems""" ;
  curric:id "241"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.582202Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-232
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Counting, recognising and comparing numbers 0 - 10"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will review their knowledge from the EYFS of counting in all its forms to and from 10. They will compare and order numbers to 10 practically and will consider the role of zero to represent nothing."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit gives pupils and teachers the opportunity to revisit and build upon the knowledge of the counting principles they have from the Early Years. It develops the use of representations that will underpin the more formal recording of maths that is to come in Year 1 and onwards whilst also providing familiar contexts for pupils just starting in KS1.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count reliably to 10 using concrete objects
Recognise and order numerals from 0 to 10
Compare quantities using language such as more, fewer, same""" ;
  curric:id "232"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.582884Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-234
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Counting to and from 20"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will consolidate counting to 20 and back They will secure their understanding of the teens numbers in a cardinal and an ordinal context."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit extends and secures the stable order principle of counting forwards and backwards to and from 20 in different contexts and from different starting points. Pupils have the opportunity to rehearse key language and to develop their understanding of how the numbers relate to different representations. This learning will be revisited and developed in later units focusing on composition of numbers to 20""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count forwards and backwards from 0 to 20
Recognise and write numerals to 20
Compare small numbers""" ;
  curric:id "234"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.583490Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-248
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Solving problems in a range of contexts"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils have the opportunity to apply their knowledge of counting, comparing and number facts to solve problems in a range of contexts."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides and opportunity to consolidate and apply a range of counting skills and number facts to solve problems. It brings together learning from previous units about numbers to 10 and 20 and counting in steps of 2, 10 and 5.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number facts and sequences
Use place value understanding
Apply basic operations in context""" ;
  curric:id "248"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.584022Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-multiplication-and-division ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-fractions ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-258
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Representing counting in 2s, 5s and 10s as the 2, 5 and 10 times tables"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will represent the 2x 10x table in different ways and use 2x 10x table to solve problems. They will explain the relationship between adjacent multiples of 2/10 and that factor pairs can be written in any order."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops understanding of multiplication and the skip counting pupils have done and applies it to the 2-, 5- and 10-times tables. They explore commutativity in that the factors can be written in any order and look at the relationship between adjacent multiples in preparation for looking for relationships between times tables in future units.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count forwards and backwards in 1s to 20
Use concrete or pictorial representations for equal groups
Recognise repeated addition patterns in numbers""" ;
  curric:id "258"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.599660Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-statistics ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-multiplication-and-division .

oakcurric:unit-255
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Calculating within 20"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will add 3 addends. They will use a strategy such as finding 2 addends to total 10 or 2 numbers to bridge though 10."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit applies known facts and explores strategies for adding within ten. Pupils use understanding of commutativity to reorder equations to calculate efficiently. The facts in this unit will then be applied to calculating beyond 20.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number bonds to 10 and 20
Use mental strategies such as counting on and bridging 10
Represent calculations with concrete or visual models""" ;
  curric:id "255"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.601737Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-statistics ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-253
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Comparing, ordering and partitioning 2-digit numbers"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will compare two 2-digit numbers and partition a 2-digit number into 10s and 1s and position on a number line."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils build on their understanding of the structure of 2-digit numbers in this unit and apply the understanding to comparing numbers and positioning them in the number system on a number line. This prepares them for applying place value understanding to calculation in future units.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count to 100
Understand place value of tens and ones
Partition numbers in different ways""" ;
  curric:id "253"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.602305Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-269
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sense of measure - capacity, volume and mass"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will choose, use and compare appropriate standard units to estimate and measure length/height mass, capacity and temperature to the nearest appropriate unit."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit highlights the need for standard units of measure and uses different contexts to introduce standard units for length, mass, capacity and temperature. Pupils estimate and measure, compare and order measurements, preparing them for applying units of measure to solve problems in various contexts in the future.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Compare and describe measures using non-standard units
Use standard units such as litres and grams
Estimate and measure using appropriate tools""" ;
  curric:id "269"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.602846Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-251
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Composition of  multiples of 10"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will represent multiples of ten using numerals and names and use knowledge of facts and unitising to add and subtract multiples of ten."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This first unit of Year 2 allows pupils to revisit Y1 learning relating to number facts within ten and how they relate to multiples of ten. This gives a familiar start and prepares them for work on numbers to 100 in the following units.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise and count in tens
Partition multiples of 10 using place value
Add and subtract tens mentally""" ;
  curric:id "251"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.608403Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-259
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Representing counting in 5s as the 5 times table and link to the 10 times tables"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will represent the 5-times table in different ways. They will explain the relationship between adjacent multiples of 5 and how 5- and 10-times tables are related.¬†"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides opportunities to rehearse the facts of the 5-times table and also to explore the link between the 5- and 10-times tables. The unit also links the times tables to multiplication contexts, identifying what the factors and product represent within the context.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count in steps of 5 and 10
Recognise patterns in number sequences
Use arrays to represent multiples""" ;
  curric:id "259"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.618816Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-statistics ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-multiplication-and-division .

oakcurric:unit-265
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Fractions: identify equal parts and be familiar with halves, thirds and quarters"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will identify whether something has or has not been split into equal parts. They will name fractions one-half one-quarter and one-third in relation to a fraction of a length shape or set of objects."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops understanding of parts and wholes, describing equal parts as fractions of a whole. Pupils then apply this to finding half of a number, relating doubling and halving to fractions. This unit prepares pupils with the language and representations for more detailed work on fractions later.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify equal parts of a whole
Name common fractions (1/2, 1/3, 1/4)
Use visual models for fractions""" ;
  curric:id "265"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.625822Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-fractions .

oakcurric:unit-244
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Composition of numbers 11 to 19"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will explain 11-19 as cardinal and ordinal numbers. They will double and halve numbers 6-9 and use addition and subtraction facts to add and subtract within 20."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces two-digit numbers between 10 and 20, rehearsing the counting sequence and beginning to explore two-digit place value, building on the counting pattern to 100 in earlier units. Here pupils will represent 2-digit numbers in different ways to show the composition of ten and a bit. Number facts to ten will be applied within 20 and doubling to ten will be extended to 20.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count and represent numbers to 10
Partition numbers into tens and ones
Use number bonds to build teen numbers""" ;
  curric:id "244"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.626351Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-237
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Comparing quantities - part part whole relationships"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will explain that items can be compared using length and height, mass and volume/capacity. They will compare sets of objects using equality/inequality symbols. Pupils will also explore part-part-whole relationships with representations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit moves on from counting to comparing items and attaching value to those items through various criteria. Equality is seen as a result of comparison and considered alongside inequality. Learning then develops to look at part-part-whole relationships using objects which are then represented with numerals. This provides the language and structure needed to move onto the following units on composition of numbers.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use bar models to compare two quantities
Understand language of comparison (more than, less than, difference)
Represent part-whole relationships using diagrams or equations""" ;
  curric:id "237"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.635090Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-238
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Composition of numbers 0 to 5"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will revisit how numbers are represented cardinally and ordinally. They will partition 1 - 5 in different ways, find a missing part when one part and the whole are known and explore one more and one less with numbers to five."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides opportunities for pupils to explore the composition of numbers to 5, representing and describing the numbers in different ways and in different contexts. In future units they will apply this to secure understanding the structures of addition and subtraction.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count reliably up to 5
Partition small numbers into parts
Recognise that the whole is made up of parts""" ;
  curric:id "238"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.640636Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-261
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Introduction to division structures"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will use practical resources to model and explain when objects can and cannot be grouped or shared equally. They will then represent practical situations using division expressions and equations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to explore equal and unequal grouping and this time relates situations to the language and symbols of division. Contexts and representations look at equal grouping and sharing. This will be developed in a future unit focusing on those two ways we can think about division.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use repeated subtraction and equal sharing
Recognise and use multiplication facts
Understand grouping and arrays in relation to division""" ;
  curric:id "261"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.641163Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-multiplication-and-division .

oakcurric:unit-235
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Counting in tens - decade numbers"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will extend their counting to counting the decade numbers which will later be known as multiples of ten and making representations of them using a variety of different manipulatives."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Patterns in the number system start from 20 but rely on children knowing the sequence of the decade numbers. This unit prepares them for counting up to 100 as they know the numbers to 20 and will be able to apply this knowledge between the decades in the following unit once the sequence of the decade numbers is secure.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Count in ones to at least 20
Recognise and name decade numbers
Understand counting patterns involving tens""" ;
  curric:id "235"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.645531Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-266
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Time: write and tell the time to five minutes"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will consolidate their understanding of time by comparing and sequencing intervals of time. They will learn to write the time to 5 minutes, including quarter past/quarter to"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on previous time learning, sequencing and also incorporates recent work on fractions to tell the time including half past and quarter past and to the hour. This will be built on in the future to tell the time to 5 minutes and calculate with time.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Read time to the hour and half hour
Understand the relationship between minutes and hours
Count in fives to track minutes on a clock face""" ;
  curric:id "266"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.648544Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-fractions .

oakcurric:unit-236
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Pattern in counting from 20 to 100"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will extend their learning by counting to 100. They will explore the pattern in counting and focus on the end of the decade and the start of the new decade numbers.¬†"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides opportunities to extend knowledge of counting in ones to counting between the decade numbers or multiples of ten. The unit also explores crossing the tens boundaries, combining knowledge of counting in ones with knowledge of the sequence of the decades both forwards and backwards. These skills are needed to compare and calculate with numbers in later units.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Confidently count in ones to 20
Recognise tens and ones in numbers to 20
Continue simple counting sequences and identify number patterns""" ;
  curric:id "236"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.650121Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-place-value .

oakcurric:unit-247
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Unitising and coin recognition - value of a set of coins"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will use knowledge of the value of coins and apply their number facts and counting skills to calculate the total value of the coins in a set of 2p 5p 10p coins.¬†"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit applies the skip counting rehearsed previously to solve problems involving numbers of coins. Pupils also have the opportunity to apply their counting and number facts knowledge to find and make amounts up to 20 p.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number facts and sequences
Use place value understanding
Apply basic operations in context""" ;
  curric:id "247"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.650655Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-262
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Shape: discuss and compare 2D and 3D shapes"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn that polygons can be described, sorted, compared and named according to the number of sides and vertices. They will describe 3D shapes, finding different ways to sort and compare them."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on sorting, classifying and pattern work, introducing more specific language and the concept of symmetry. It gives pupils the language needed to explore, describe and classify other shapes and their features in future units.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Name and identify common 2D and 3D shapes
Describe properties such as sides, edges, faces, and vertices
Sort shapes based on visual or physical characteristics""" ;
  curric:id "262"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.659859Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-250
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Time - sequencing events and telling the time to the hour and half hour"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will sequence events in chronological order and recognise and use language relating to dates. They will tell the time to the hour and half past the hour linking to fractions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds both on sequencing events and language relating to dates from Early Years to include the days of the week and months of the year. The unit also builds on the fractional language of position and direction. Pupils apply this to telling the time to the hour and half hour.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Read time to the hour and half hour
Understand 12-hour clock notation
Convert between hours and minutes""" ;
  curric:id "250"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.665796Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-254
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Secure fluency of addition and subtraction facts within 10"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will revisit addition and subtraction within ten. They will consolidate addition and subtraction strategies."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In preparation for calculating to and beyond 20, this unit allows pupils to review and secure addition facts within ten so that they can apply them to calculating beyond ten in the following units.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number facts and sequences
Use place value understanding
Apply basic operations in context""" ;
  curric:id "254"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.666302Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-addition-and-subtraction .

oakcurric:unit-249
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Position and direction including fractions of turns"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will describe position direction and movement including whole half quarter and three-quarter turns.¬†"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on position, direction and spatial reasoning work in the Early Years. The learning is developed to include the ideas of turns that are a fraction of a whole to describe position and movement.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use directional language (left, right, turn)
Recognise quarter, half and full turns
Represent turns using fractions""" ;
  curric:id "249"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.666800Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-fractions .

oakcurric:unit-260
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Multiplying by 2, doubling and halving (factors and products)"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how multiplication with 2 as a factor relates to doubling and how we can see halving as the inverse of doubling, deriving the related halving fact from a known double."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit focuses on the fact that, when one of the factors is 2, we can think about doubling. Pupils also relate the factor being doubled to being half of the product and use this to solve problems and identify missing factors. Exploring the inverse of multiplication will lead on to exploring division structures in the next unit.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recall number facts and sequences
Use place value understanding
Apply basic operations in context""" ;
  curric:id "260"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.671487Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number ,
    oakcurric:thread-number-fractions .

